SIMPLE: scribbling
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scribbling
<hw>Scrib"bling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 1st
<er>Scribble</er>.]</ety> <def>The act or process of carding
coarsely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scribbling machine</b></col>, <cd>the machine used for
the first carding of wool or other fiber; -- called also
<altname>scribbler</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scribbling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scribbling
<hw>Scrib"bling</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Writing hastily or
poorly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye newspaper witlings! ye pert <qex>scribbling</qex> folks!</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scribbling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Scribbling
<hw>Scrib"bling</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of writing hastily or
idly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scribblingly</ent>⟦br⟧
